                           DESCRiPTiON 
                          
Actor and wheelchair sportsman Peter Mitchell, who was paralysed in a car 
crash, follows the stories of three young people who have battled to survive a 
life-changing illness or injury and are fighting to access the support they 
need to live the life they want. He meets Billy, from Sussex, who found himself 
discharged from hospital into a hotel because of a lack of accessible 
accommodation, and travels to Stirling to find Helen; who didn't qualify for 
any benefits despite being newly disabled and having to leave her job. Peter 
also meets Jacob, from Preston, who made the decision to have his legs 
amputated following a battle with meningitis and who is discovering that 
without an accessible car, he is stranded in his own home.
